 Cradock - Police in Cradock on Tuesday made an appeal to the public for assistance with information on murder cases reported on Sunday and Monday. "On Sunday, at about 08:40, a police official, who was on his way to the police station driving in Cross Street noticed a person lying next to the wall outside Goniwe's Tavern in Cross Street," said police spokesperson, Captain Lariane Jonker. "On further investigation, the police official noticed that it was a female with several stab wounds to her upper body. "She was certified dead by paramedics on the scene of the crime." Captain Jonker said that during another incident on Monday, at about 06:10am, the body of a man was found in a open field next to the N10, National road. "On arrival of the ambulance services on the scene, the victim was lying face down and badly beaten with stones. He was also certified dead, on the scene of the crime." Anyone with information is requested to contact Detective Constable Ntsimango at the Cradock Detective Unit on cell phone: 078 084 9136. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 